    "content_hash": "54b3e127deebef19",
    "department": "Marketing",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is seeking a dynamic and results-oriented Partner Marketing Program Manager - to join our EMEA partner marketing team. In this pivotal role, you will be instrumental in maximizing the value and impact of our alliances with one of our cloud partners (AWS).\n\nThis role focuses heavily on execution, governance, and enablement, ensuring our high-touch field activities with AWS are flawlessly managed and aligned with our broader strategic Go-To-Market (GTM) motions. You will serve as the dedicated point of contact for our Alliances and Field Teams to ensure local field events are funded, approved, and executed without bottlenecks. As part of the role, you will also work on marketing - through campaigns aligned to Snowflake’s top priorities.\n\nSuccess in this role hinges on exceptional cross-functional collaboration. You will work closely with marketing, alliances, and sales teams.\n\nThis position has a hybrid work schedule requiring 3 days per week in Snowflake’s London office.\n\n\nAS A PARTNER MARKETING PROGRAM MANAGER - AWS AT SNOWFLAKE, YOU WILL:\n\n - Manage effective MDF spend against AWS and Snowflake’s priorities\n\n - Measure Success: Establish goals and track the performance of all partner marketing initiatives to make a meaningful difference in Snowflake's business.\n\n - Build Pipeline: Design, execute, and manage innovative marketing through campaigns for our partners that deliver measurable results.\n\n - Influence and Align Cross-Functionally: Embed our cloud partnerships within Snowflake’s highly cross-functional working teams, collaborating across cloud alliances, product marketing, field marketing, demand gen, content, PR, and social.\n\n\nOUR IDEAL SENIOR PARTNER MARKETING MANAGER WILL HAVE:\n\n - Relevant Experience: 5+ years of marketing or alliances experience, preferably high-growth, successful, B2B tech companies. Product or partner marketing background preferred.\n\n - Strategic Vision \u0026 Tactical Execution: Exhibits the ability to think strategically about full-funnel pipeline development while also being highly adept at hands-on execution and tactical problem-solving to ensure initiatives deliver tangible results.\n\n - Exceptional Influencer \u0026 Communicator: A natural storyteller and persuasive influencer, skilled at crafting clear, concise, and impactful messages for diverse internal and external audiences.\n\n - An 'Own It' Mentality: A proactive mindset with a bias for action and the ability to act decisively, take initiative, and move projects forward efficiently.\n\n - Cross-Functional Excellence: Proven ability to thrive in a highly cross-functional and matrixed environment with numerous internal and external stakeholders.\n\n - Big Picture Thinking: The ability to think big and re-imagine how Snowflake can deliver value to customers in collaboration with our partner ecosystem.\n\n - Education: Bachelor’s degree in Marketing, Business, or a related field.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
